---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'February 25, 2026';
---
<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — TechMo Electronics"
  description="Read TechMo's Privacy Policy. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your personal data."
  canonical="/privacy-policy"
>
  <Navbar />

  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-r from-[#0f172a] to-[#1e3a8a] text-white py-14 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <div class="text-5xl mb-3" aria-hidden="true">🔒</div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-blue-200">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="py-14 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose-custom">

      <div class="notice-box">
        <strong>Your privacy matters to us.</strong> This Privacy Policy explains how TechMo Enterprise
        (Pvt) Ltd ("TechMo", "we", "our", or "us") collects, uses, stores, and protects your
        personal data when you visit our website, make a purchase, or use our repair services.
      </div>

      <section aria-labelledby="section-1">
        <h2 id="section-1">1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <h3>1.1 Information you provide directly</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact details:</strong> Name, phone number, email address, and delivery address when you make an inquiry, purchase, or booking.</li>
          <li><strong>Device details:</strong> IMEI numbers, serial numbers, and device model information required for warranty registration and repair services.</li>
          <li><strong>Repair information:</strong> Device condition, reported faults, and any accessories or items left with us.</li>
          <li><strong>Loyalty programme:</strong> Account details including purchase history, earned points, and tier status.</li>
          <li><strong>Payment details:</strong> Payment method type (cash, card) — we do <strong>not</strong> store card numbers or banking credentials.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.2 Information collected automatically</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> Pages visited, time on site, and interaction with our content — collected via Cloudflare Web Analytics (cookie-free, GDPR-compliant).</li>
          <li><strong>Device & browser data:</strong> Browser type, OS, and screen resolution for website optimisation.</li>
          <li><strong>IP address:</strong> Used for security purposes and DDoS protection via Cloudflare.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="section-2">
        <h2 id="section-2">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To process purchases, issue invoices, and fulfil orders</li>
          <li>To manage repair tickets and send you real-time status updates</li>
          <li>To validate warranty claims using IMEI/serial numbers</li>
          <li>To manage your loyalty points account and send reward notifications</li>
          <li>To respond to inquiries and provide customer support</li>
          <li>To send transactional emails (invoice copies, repair updates, receipts)</li>
          <li>To improve our website, products, and services</li>
          <li>To comply with legal and regulatory obligations</li>
          <li>To protect against fraud, abuse, and security threats</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="section-3">
        <h2 id="section-3">3. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)</h2>
        <p>We process your personal data on the following legal bases:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contract performance:</strong> To fulfil purchases, repairs, and service agreements</li>
          <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> To improve our services, prevent fraud, and ensure security</li>
          <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> To comply with tax, consumer protection, and other applicable laws</li>
          <li><strong>Consent:</strong> Where you have opted in to marketing communications</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="section-4">
        <h2 id="section-4">4. Data Sharing & Third Parties</h2>
        <p>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data. We may share data with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cloudflare:</strong> For CDN, DDoS protection, analytics, and bot protection (privacy-first, no personal data used in analytics)</li>
          <li><strong>Cloudinary:</strong> For storage and delivery of invoice PDFs and receipt images</li>
          <li><strong>SMTP provider (Gmail/custom):</strong> To send transactional emails on our behalf</li>
          <li><strong>Legal authorities:</strong> If required by law, court order, or to protect our legal rights</li>
        </ul>
        <p>All third-party processors are bound by data processing agreements and appropriate safeguards.</p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="section-5">
        <h2 id="section-5">5. Data Retention</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Transaction records:</strong> Retained for 7 years to comply with tax regulations</li>
          <li><strong>Repair records:</strong> Retained for the duration of the applicable warranty period plus 2 years</li>
          <li><strong>Inquiry data:</strong> Retained for 12 months unless converted to a customer account</li>
          <li><strong>Loyalty account:</strong> Retained while your account is active; deleted 3 years after last activity upon request</li>
          <li><strong>Website analytics:</strong> Aggregated, non-personal data; retained indefinitely</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="section-6">
        <h2 id="section-6">6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Depending on your location, you may have the following rights:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Right of access:</strong> Request a copy of your personal data</li>
          <li><strong>Right to rectification:</strong> Correct inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
          <li><strong>Right to erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your data (subject to legal retention requirements)</li>
          <li><strong>Right to restriction:</strong> Limit how we process your data</li>
          <li><strong>Right to data portability:</strong> Receive your data in a portable format</li>
          <li><strong>Right to object:</strong> Object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
          <li><strong>Right to withdraw consent:</strong> Where consent is the legal basis</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise any right, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@techmo.lk">privacy@techmo.lk</a>. We will respond within 30 days.</p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="section-7">
        <h2 id="section-7">7. Security</h2>
        <p>We implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect your data, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>TLS 1.3 encryption for all data in transit</li>
          <li>Encrypted databases with access controls</li>
          <li>Role-based access control (RBAC) limiting staff data access</li>
          <li>Immutable audit logs for all sensitive operations</li>
          <li>Cloudflare WAF and DDoS protection</li>
          <li>Regular security assessments</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="section-8">
        <h2 id="section-8">8. Cookies & Tracking</h2>
        <p>Our website uses minimal tracking. Please see our <a href="/cookies">Cookie Policy</a> for full details.
        We use Cloudflare Web Analytics, which is cookie-free and does not track individuals.</p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="section-9">
        <h2 id="section-9">9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>Our services are not directed to individuals under 16 years of age. We do not knowingly collect
        personal data from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal data, please
        contact us immediately.</p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="section-10">
        <h2 id="section-10">10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Material changes will be notified via our website
        with an updated "last updated" date. Your continued use of our services after changes constitutes
        acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="section-11">
        <h2 id="section-11">11. Contact Us</h2>
        <div class="contact-card">
          <p><strong>TechMo Enterprise (Pvt) Ltd</strong><br />
          45 Galle Road, Colombo 03, Sri Lanka</p>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@techmo.lk">privacy@techmo.lk</a><br />
          Phone: <a href="tel:+94112345678">+94 11 234 5678</a><br />
          Hours: Monday – Saturday, 9am – 7pm</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mt-10 pt-6 border-t border-gray-100">
        <a href="/terms" class="policy-link">Terms of Service →</a>
        <a href="/cookies" class="policy-link">Cookie Policy →</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="policy-link">Contact Us →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose-custom { @apply text-[#334155] leading-relaxed; }
  .prose-custom h2 {
    @apply text-xl font-bold text-[#0f172a] mt-10 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-100;
  }
  .prose-custom h3 { @apply text-base font-semibold text-[#0f172a] mt-5 mb-2; }
  .prose-custom p { @apply mb-4 text-[15px]; }
  .prose-custom ul { @apply list-disc pl-5 space-y-1.5 mb-4 text-[15px]; }
  .prose-custom li { @apply text-[#334155]; }
  .prose-custom a { @apply text-[#1e40af] hover:underline font-medium; }
  .notice-box {
    @apply bg-blue-50 border border-blue-100 rounded-xl p-5 mb-8 text-sm text-[#334155];
  }
  .contact-card {
    @apply bg-[#f8fafc] rounded-xl border border-gray-100 p-5 mt-3 text-sm;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  .policy-link {
    @apply inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-medium text-[#1e40af]
           hover:text-[#1e3a8a] transition-colors;
  }
</style>
